29/05/2005
PARIS, France -- Minister of Foreign Trade Francois Loos assured Macedonian Economy Minister Fatmir Besimi that France supports Skopje's bid for EU accession, during a meeting Friday (27 May). 
Loos implied that France would lobby in favour of a positive European Commission stance on Macedonia's application to obtain official EU candidate member status.
Also Friday, Macedonian Deputy Prime Minister Radmila Sekerinska said she and Bulgarian Minister for EU Affairs Meglena Kuneva discussed Sofia's possible assistance with expertise in the EU integration process. 
They also discussed regional co-operation issues. 
(Vecer - 28/05/05; Macedonian Government Web site - 27/05/05)
